=Description=

"The modern D21 - Janeček voting method, we seek solutions most people can agree on.

Benefits of our method:

* Finds the widest possible common consensus.
* Uncovers controversial possibilities.
* Enables citizens to express more precisely.
* Is simple and intuitive.

D21 - Janeček method is a modern voting and electoral method making any group decision more effective. It enables casting multiple votes, and in certain cases, also a minus vote. 

Multiple votes enable us to express a wider scope of preferences, thereby reflecting the complexities of social choice more accurately."

(https://www.ih21.org/en/d21-janecekmethod)

